{"id":"beeves","term":"Beeves","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>(an old English plural of the word beef), a name applicable to all ruminating animals except camels, and especially to the Bovidce, or horned cattle (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Leviticus 22:19\">Lev. 22:19</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Leviticus 22:21\">21</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 31:28\">Num. 31:28</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 31:30\">30</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 31:33\">33</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 31:38\">38</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Numbers 31:44\">44</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Leviticus 22:19","Leviticus 22:21","Numbers 31:28","Numbers 31:30","Numbers 31:33","Numbers 31:38","Numbers 31:44"]}